But there is also a more particular allusion to the penetralia or shrine within the atrium of the Vestals, in which were stored the most holy pledges of Rome’s existence, among them the Palladium: cs. 5. 52. 7. None might enter here except the Pontifices and the Vestals, whereas the Temple of Vesta with the perpetual fire was accessible to the general public.
